            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-09-23 10:51:23" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to cause something to pass through the mouth and into the stomach</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to swallow</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The saying about ‘straining out a fly and swallowing a camel’ refers to gross unawareness of inconsistencies in one’s behavior, but in translating it is far better to preserve the intentional hyperbole, since it is one which can be readily grasped. As an aid to the reader, one can refer to the fact that in the list of unclean animals in {S:00301100000000}, the fly or gnat is the smallest and the camel is the largest.</Comments>
